1 A RESOLUTION
2 To express the condolences of the House of Representatives on the tragic loss of eight
3 children in Shreveport, Louisiana.
4 WHEREAS, it is with immense sadness and profound regret that the House of
5 Representatives of the Legislature of Louisiana has learned of the tragic passing, on
6 April 19, 2026, of Layla Pugh, Kayla Pugh, Shayla Elkins, Jayla Elkins, Sariahh Snow,
7 Khedarrion Snow, Braylon Snow, and Mar'Kaydon Pugh; and
8 WHEREAS, Layla Pugh was a second-grade student at Linwood Public Charter
9 School; she was a quiet girl who always strived to do the right thing; she was a friend to
10 everyone and a constant help to her teachers and classmates; and
11 WHEREAS, Kayla Pugh was a first-grade student at Linwood Public Charter School;
12 although she was a soft-spoken child, her smile spoke louder than any words; she lit up
13 every room she entered and gave the biggest hugs when greeting her teachers and principal;
14 and
15 WHEREAS, Shayla Elkins was a kindergarten student at Linwood Public Charter
16 School; she was soft spoken, had a quiet presence, and gave warm and welcoming hugs; and
17 WHEREAS, Jayla Elkins was a sweet child who was only three years old; and
18 WHEREAS, Sariahh Snow was a fourth-grade student at Summer Grove Elementary
19 School; she was a friend to everyone she met, was not afraid of hard work, and gave her best
