1 effort in all that she did; she was always excited to learn, had the most beautiful smile, and
2 showed kindness to students and teachers alike; and
3 WHEREAS, Khedarrion Snow was a kindergarten student at Summer Grove
4 Elementary School; he was a vibrant soul with a curious mind and fearless heart and had a
5 way of bringing a smile to anyone he met; he found joy in every moment and had a thirst for
6 adventure and desire to learn more about the world; he brought unique energy to every circle
7 he joined and cherished the time he spent with his friends and classmates; and
8 WHEREAS, Braylon Snow was a pre-kindergarten student at Johnnie Cochran Head
9 Start Center; and
10 WHEREAS, Mar'Kaydon Pugh was a fourth-grade student at Linwood Public
11 Charter School; he arrived at school with a Bible in hand each day and was passionate about
12 his faith; he frequently read his Bible during lunch or enrichment class, and poured his heart
13 into every hug that he gave; and
14 WHEREAS, although the children will be deeply missed, the memory of their spirits
15 shall live on in the hearts and minds of those who were privileged to have known and loved
16 them.
17 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
18 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby express heartfelt condolences on the loss of Layla
19 Pugh, Kayla Pugh, Shayla Elkins, Jayla Elkins, Sariahh Snow, Khedarrion Snow, Braylon
20 Snow, and Mar'Kaydon Pugh and does hereby extend sincere wishes that their family,
21 friends, and loved ones find comfort in their shared memories of these eight beautiful angels.
